\subsection{Context}

\par
This incident occurred during the January 2025 Los Angeles wildfires when a Quebec government CL-415 "Super Scooper" firefighting aircraft collided with an unknown unmanned aircraft system (UAS) while conducting aerial firefighting operations. The UAS was destroyed; the CL-415 sustained minor damage and both crew members were uninjured.
\par
The incident has been classified as a "security/criminal event" and jurisdiction was transferred to the FBI, indicating potential criminal investigation into the drone operation in restricted airspace during emergency firefighting operations.
\par
\subsection{Key Points for Research}

\begin{enumerate}

\item \textbf{First documented mid-air collision} between a firefighting aircraft and UAS during active fire suppression operations
\item \textbf{UAS characteristics:} 4-engine configuration suggests a larger commercial or custom-built drone
\item \textbf{FBI jurisdiction} suggests potential criminal prosecution under 18 U.S.C. \S{} 32 (destruction of aircraft) or related statutes
\item \textbf{No probable cause determination} by NTSB due to FBI taking lead
\item \textbf{Foreign aircraft involvement:} Canadian provincial government aircraft operating under COA in U.S. airspace
\item \textbf{TFR violations:} Likely violation of temporary flight restrictions established for firefighting operations

