\subsubsection{Heatmap Development Method}

\par
Pitcher contracted a freelance developer via Fiverr (\$41.80 total) using this workflow:
\par
\begin{enumerate}

\item \textbf{Geolocate:} Convert (city, state) to (latitude, longitude)
\item \textbf{Load:} Import points as CSV into QGIS; export as GeoJSON
\item \textbf{Webmap:} Create using Leaflet JavaScript library
\item \textbf{Count:} Calculate sightings per location for hot/cold points
\item \textbf{Visualize:} Apply plugins for cluster and heatmap views
\item \textbf{Code:} Write webmap code in text editor

\end{enumerate}

\par
\textbf{Tool:} QGIS (open-source GIS software) \textbf{Output:} Chrome HTML document with three result types: heatmap, point clusters, individual points
\par
\subsection{Critical Analysis}

\subsubsection{Strengths}

\begin{itemize}

\item \textbf{Large dataset:} 9,467 reports across 5 complete years
\item \textbf{Mixed methods:} Combines statistical rigor with qualitative context
\item \textbf{Rich visualizations:} GIS heatmaps provide intuitive geographic understanding
\item \textbf{Validated statistics:} Chi-Square tests meet critical values for state and temporal analyses

\end{itemize}

\subsubsection{Limitations}

\begin{enumerate}

\item \textbf{Reporting bias:} "Only individuals familiar with UAS who know how to file a report, or those who care to file a sighting report on unauthorized UAS usage will make it into the reported data" (p. 206)
\item \textbf{Census data age:} 2010 Census used for 2015--2019 analysis (nearly 10 years old)
\item \textbf{Weather microclimate:} Data may not represent entire metropolitan areas
\item \textbf{Causality ambiguity:} Cannot distinguish between more flights occurring vs. more people available to report
\item \textbf{COVID exclusion:} 2020 data excluded, limiting pandemic-era insights

\end{enumerate}

